375 g Hayter's Turkey Maple Breakfast Sausages
350 g Gnocchi
1 unit(s) Delicata Squash
113 g Yellow Onion, chopped
113 g Kale, chopped
7 g Parsley
1 unit(s) Lemon
113 mL Cream
½ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
1 tbsp Cream Sauce Spice Blend
½ tsp Pumpkin Pie Spice Mix
4.5 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Carefully halve squash lengthwise. (TIP: Insert tip of the knife in the middle of the squash, then cut one end in half. Repeat on other end.)
Scoop out seeds and pulp with a spoon, then discard.
Working with one half at a time, place squash on cutting board, cut-side down. You will have four quarters (eight quarters for 4 ppl).
Cut each quarter into 1/2-inch slices crosswise.

Add squash, half the Pumpkin Pie Spice Mix (use all for 4 ppl) and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter to an 8x8-inch baking dish (9x13-inch baking dish for 4 ppl). Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven, tossing halfway through, until golden and tender, 20-25 min.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
While the pan heats, remove sausage meat from its casing and transfer to a plate.
When the pan is hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) butter, then sausage. Cook, breaking up sausage into smaller pieces, until golden-brown and cooked through, 5-7 min.**
Remove from heat, then transfer cooked sausage to a bowl.

Reheat the same pan over medium.
When hot, add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter, then gnocchi. Cook, tossing often, until golden, 4-6 min.
Meanwhile, remove any large pieces of stem from kale.
Add kale to pan with gnocchi. Season with salt and pepper. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until gnocchi is golden-brown and kale is tender, 2-3 min.
Remove from heat, then transfer gnocchi and kale to bowl with sausage.

Reheat the same pan over medium.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, then onions. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until tender, 3-4 min.
Sprinkle Cream Sauce Spice Blend over top. Stir until onions are coated, 30 sec.
Add cream and 1/2 cup (3/4 cup) water. Bring to a simmer. Cook, stirring often, unti thickened, 1-3 min.

Add gnocchi, kale, sausages and half the Parmesan to pan with sauce. Cook, stirring often, until warmed through, 1-2 min. (TIP: If you prefer a lighter sauce, add warm water, 1-2 tbsp at a time.)
Roughly chop parsley.
Divide gnocchi, sausages and sauce between plates.
Top with squash.
Sprinkle parsley and remaining Parmesan over top.
Zest half the lemon over plates of gnocchi. Cut lemon into wedges and squeeze over top, if desired.